We start by writing down each “lineage statement” as a relation (using “A → B” to mean “A is an ancestor of B”):

• Statement 11 tells us that Harold is an ancestor of Jeffrey.
• Statement 13 tells us that Jeffrey is an ancestor of Lisa, so the chain is:
  Harold → Jeffrey → Lisa → … → (other people in that branch).
• Continuing from Lisa, statement 42 gives:
  Lisa → Elijah, and then statement 21 gives:
  Elijah → Ryan, then statement 27 gives:
  Ryan → Kathleen, and statement 50 gives:
  Kathleen → Cheryl.
This branch (Harold, Jeffrey, Lisa, Elijah, Ryan, Kathleen, Cheryl) contains no other mention of the names we’re comparing.

Meanwhile, looking at Janet we note:
• Statement 52 tells us “Douglas is Janet’s descendant,” which means:
  Janet → Douglas.
• Then statement 29 tells us “Karen is Douglas’s descendant”, so
  Janet → … → Douglas → Karen.
• Several further relations are given that connect Karen (and her descendants) with many others. In fact, following the chain (via statements 57, 53, 33, 14, 8, 44, 48, 18, 24, 40, 20, 51, 56, 3, 47, 12, 46, 58, 45, 19, 34, 30, 38, 55, 15, 41, 9, 7, 22) we eventually see that Janet is the ancestor of many individuals (Douglas, Karen, Debra, Christina, Lauren, Sara, Hannah, Helen, Richard, Ruth, Martha, Sophia, Austin, Joseph, Raymond, Sean, Jean, Billy, Albert, Wayne, Robert, Grace, Larry, Rachel, Marilyn, Jennifer, Andrew, Abigail, Judith, Amber, George).

When comparing the two “trees” we have built it is clear that:
– In the Harold branch the members are Harold, Jeffrey, Lisa, Elijah, Ryan, Kathleen, Cheryl.
– In the Janet branch the members include a long list that does not incorporate any of the names from the Harold branch.
There is no statement linking any person in Harold’s branch with any person in Janet’s branch. None of the given relations tell us that Janet is either an ancestor or descendant of Harold, nor is there a statement showing a merging of the two families (for instance, having a common descendant).

Thus, based solely on the provided relationships no connection between Janet and Harold can be deduced. That is, the answer is:

<ANSWER>5</ANSWER>
